        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:28PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurel Hill, or 7 miles southwest of Florala, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Laurel Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
